@startuml fig-cidr-subnetting
'A4 Portrait
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false

title CIDR Subnetting Workflow

start

:Given: Network to subnet
Example: 192.168.1.0/24
Need: 4 subnets;

:Calculate bits needed
----
4 subnets = 2^n
n = 2 bits borrowed;

:New prefix length
----
Original: /24
Borrowed: 2 bits
New: /24 + 2 = /26;

:Calculate subnet size
----
Host bits: 32 - 26 = 6
Hosts per subnet: 2^6 - 2 = 62;

:List subnets
----
Subnet 0: 192.168.1.0/26
  Range: .1 - .62
  Broadcast: .63

Subnet 1: 192.168.1.64/26
  Range: .65 - .126
  Broadcast: .127

Subnet 2: 192.168.1.128/26
  Range: .129 - .190
  Broadcast: .191

Subnet 3: 192.168.1.192/26
  Range: .193 - .254
  Broadcast: .255;

stop

note right
    Quick Reference:
    /24 = 254 hosts
    /25 = 126 hosts
    /26 = 62 hosts
    /27 = 30 hosts
    /28 = 14 hosts
    /29 = 6 hosts
    /30 = 2 hosts
end note

